{"title_page": "Bost University", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            = Bost University \n|native_name     =  Bost University \u0628\u064f\u0633\u062a \u067e\u0648\u0647\u0646\u062a\u0648\u0646\n|latin_name      = \n|image           = BOST.JPG\n|image_size      = 220\n|caption         = Bost University, Helmand\n|motto           = \u06a9\u06cc\u0641\u06cc\u062a \u0632\u0645\u0648\u0696 \u0644\u0648\u0645\u0693\u06cc\u062a\u0648\u0628 \u062f\u06cc\n|motto_lang      = pus\n|mottoeng        = ''Quality is our Priority''\n|established     = 2012-1391\n|type            = Private\n|endowment       =\n|faculty        = Engineering, Law & Political Science, Economics, Medicine, Computer Science, Midwife, Nursing, Laboratory, Physiotherapy, Dentistry & Pharmacy\n|president       = Diplom Engineer Mahmood Sangin\n|provost         =\n|student_body_president=\n|student_body_vice_president=\n|principal       =\n|rector          =\n|vice_chancellor = Abdullah Zeyayee Academic\n|dean            =\n|head_label      =\n|head            =\n|students        =\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|profess         =\n|city            = [[Lashkargah]]\n|state           = [[Helmand]]\n|country         = [[Afghanistan]]\n|campus          =\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|colors          = Black, red, and green {{Color box|black|border=darkgray}}{{Color box|red|border=darkgray}}{{Color box|green|border=darkgray}}\n|mascot          =\n|nickname        =\n|affiliations    =\n|footnotes       =\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.bost.edu.af/}}\n|coor            = {{coord|31|51|24|N|064|13|15|E|display=inline,title|type:edu}}\n}}\n'''Bost University''' ({{lang-ps| \u0628\u064f\u0633\u062a \u067e\u0648\u0647\u0646\u062a\u0648\u0646}}) in [[Lashkargah]], [[Helmand Province]], [[Afghanistan]] is a private institution of higher education founded by Ahmad Jan Popal in 1391-2012. Bost University offers two- to six-year undergraduate degrees and diplomas. Four- to six-year undergraduate programs are included in Engineering, Law & Political Science, Economics, Medicine, Computer Science.\n\nCertificates for short-term courses and training that are three years or less are part of the university's Institute of Health Science such as Midwife, Nursing, Laboratory, Physiotherapy, Dentistry & Pharmacy.\n\n==History==\nFrom the beginning it was the Bost Institute of Higher Education. In 2013 the Ministry of Higher Education Quality Commission Board investigated all the private universities in the country. In 2015 the board announced its results and Bost Institute of Higher Education got the top marks (88.3) and was announced the top university of all private universities in Afghanistan.\n\nThe Ministry of Higher Education promoted the university to Bost University (\u0628\u064f\u0633\u062a \u067e\u0648\u0647\u0646\u062a\u0648\u0646) awarded in November 2015.\n\n==Faculties and departments==\n* Faculty of Law and Political Science\n**Law\n**Management (Political Science)\n* Faculty of Economics\n**Statistics\n**Finance\n**Business Administration\n**Economics\n* Faculty of Engineering\n**Architecture\n**Civil\n**Mechanical\n**Electrical Engineering\n* Faculty of Medicine, six-year program in General Medicine\n* Faculty of Computer Science\n**Hardware\n**Software\n\n==Institute of Health Science==\n* Nursing (NRS): three-year program\n* Midwife (MW): two-year program\n* Laboratory (LAB): two-year program\n* Pharmacy (PHR): two-year program\n* Physiotherapy (PTR): two-year program\n* Dentistry (DNT): two-year program\n\n==Library==\nThe library has more than 8000 Pashto, Dari, and English books.\n\n==Laboratory==\nThe university has a laboratory for its engineering faculty students.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of universities in Afghanistan]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.mohe.gov.af/ Official website of Ministry of Higher Education]\n*[http://mohe.gov.af/?p=private]\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bost University}}\n*[http://www.bost.edu.af/ Official website of Bost University]\n*[http://www.mohe.gov.af/p_university/da]\n*[http://www.4icu.org/af/]\n*[[List of universities in Afghanistan]]\n\n{{Afghan universities}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Helmand Province]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Afghanistan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox university\n|name            = Bost University \n|native_name     =  Bost University \u0628\u064f\u0633\u062a \u067e\u0648\u0647\u0646\u062a\u0648\u0646\n|latin_name      = \n|image           = BOST.JPG\n|image_size      = 220\n|caption         = Bost University, Helmand\n|motto           = \u06a9\u06cc\u0641\u06cc\u062a \u0632\u0645\u0648\u0696 \u0644\u0648\u0645\u0693\u06cc\u062a\u0648\u0628 \u062f\u06cc\n|motto_lang      = pus\n|mottoeng        = ''Quality is our Priority''\n|established     = 2012-1391\n|type            = Private\n|endowment       =\n|faculty        = Engineering, Law & Political Science, Economics, Medicine, Computer Science, Midwife, Nursing, Laboratory, Physiotherapy, Dentistry & Pharmacy\n|president       = Diplom Engineer Mahmood Sangin\n|provost         =\n|student_body_president=\n|student_body_vice_president=\n|principal       =\n|rector          =\n|vice_chancellor = Abdullah Zeyayee Academic\n|dean            =\n|head_label      =\n|head            =\n|students        =\n|undergrad       =\n|postgrad        =\n|doctoral        =\n|profess         =\n|city            = [[Lashkargah]]\n|state           = [[Helmand]]\n|country         = [[Afghanistan]]\n|campus          =\n|free_label      =\n|free            =\n|colors          = Black, red, and green {{Color box|black|border=darkgray}}{{Color box|red|border=darkgray}}{{Color box|green|border=darkgray}}\n|mascot          =\n|nickname        =\n|affiliations    =\n|footnotes       =\n|website         = {{URL|http://www.bost.edu.af/}}\n|coor            = {{coord|31|51|24|N|064|13|15|E|display=inline,title|type:edu}}\n}}\n'''Bost University''' ({{lang-ps| \u0628\u064f\u0633\u062a \u067e\u0648\u0647\u0646\u062a\u0648\u0646}}) in [[Lashkargah]], [[Helmand Province]], [[Afghanistan]] is a private institution of higher education founded by Ahmad Jan Popal in 1391-2012. Bost University offers two- to six-year undergraduate degrees and diplomas. Four- to six-year undergraduate programs are included in Engineering, Law & Political Science, Economics, Medicine, Computer Science.\n\nCertificates for short-term courses and training that are three years or less are part of the university's Institute of Health Science such as Midwife, Nursing, Laboratory, Physiotherapy, Dentistry & Pharmacy.\n\n==History==\nFrom the beginning it was the Bost Institute of Higher Education. In 2013 the Ministry of Higher Education Quality Commission Board investigated all the private universities in the country. In 2015 the board announced its results and Bost Institute of Higher Education got the top marks (88.3) and was announced the top university of all private universities in Afghanistan.\n\nThe Ministry of Higher Education promoted the university to Bost University (\u0628\u064f\u0633\u062a \u067e\u0648\u0647\u0646\u062a\u0648\u0646) awarded in November 2015.\n\n==Faculties and departments==\n* Faculty of Law and Political Science\n**Law\n**Management (Political Science)\n* Faculty of Economics\n**Statistics\n**Finance\n**Business Administration\n**Economics\n* Faculty of Engineering\n**Architecture\n**Civil\n**Mechanical\n**Electrical Engineering\n* Faculty of Medicine, six-year program in General Medicine\n* Faculty of Computer Science\n**Hardware\n**Software\n\n==Institute of Health Science==\n* Nursing (NRS): three-year program\n* Midwife (MW): two-year program\n* Laboratory (LAB): two-year program\n* Pharmacy (PHR): two-year program\n* Physiotherapy (PTR): two-year program\n* Dentistry (DNT): two-year program\n\n==Library==\nThe library has more than 8000 Pashto, Dari, and English books.\n\n==Laboratory==\nThe university has a laboratory for its engineering faculty students.\n\n== See also ==\n*[[List of universities in Afghanistan]]\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.mohe.gov.af/ Official website of Ministry of Higher Education]\n*[http://mohe.gov.af/?p=private]\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bost University}}\n*[http://www.bost.edu.af/ Official website of Bost University]\n*[http://www.mohe.gov.af/p_university/da]\n*[http://www.4icu.org/af/]\n*[[List of universities in Afghanistan]]\n\n{{Afghan universities}}\n\n[[Category:Universities in Afghanistan]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Helmand Province]]\n[[Category:2012 establishments in Afghanistan]]\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bost_University"}
{"title_page": "Anthony Alonzo", "text_new": "{{short description|Filipino actor, singer, and politician}}{{More citations needed|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name        = Anthony Alonzo\n|image       =\n|caption     =\n|birth_name  = Antonio Viana Hernandez\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date|1948|4|2}}\n|birth_place = [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n|death_date  = {{Death date and age|1998|10|9|1948|4|2}}\n|death_place = [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n|other_names = Tonio, Tony\n|known_for   = Former action star\n|occupation  = Actor, politician, singer\n|yearsactive = 1974\u20131998\n|nationality = [[Philippine nationality law|Filipino]]\n|parents     = {{ubl|Alfredo Hernandez {{small|(father)}}|Lourdes Viana {{small|(mother)}}}}\n|relatives   = {{ubl|[[Alicia Alonzo]] {{small|(sister)}}|[[Jon Hernandez]] {{small|(nephew)}}}}\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Viana Alonzo''' (April 2, 1948 \u2013 October 9, 1998), also known as '''Anthony''' and '''Tony''', was a Filipino actor, singer, and councilor of [[Quezon City]].\n\n==Early life==\nHe was born as Antonio Viana Hernandez on April 2, 1948, in [[Quezon City]] to Alfredo Hernandez and Lourdes Viana. He is the brother of actress [[Alicia Alonzo]], who herself is still appearing in Filipino films and soaps.\n\n==Education==\nAntonio V. Hernandez received his elementary and secondary education at the Marulas Elementary School and Espiritu Santo High School, respectively. He took up Commerce at the Mapua Institute of Technology.\n\n==Movie career==\nBesides the so-called bold and sexy films that pervaded the movie industry in the '70s and early '80s, the period also saw the emergence and proliferation of true-to-life movies. Producers then banked on the colorful and controversial lives of known notorious criminals to come up with profitable movie projects, i.e. Nardong Putik, Kapitan Eddie Set, Baby Ama, Ronquillo, Salonga, and Waway, to name a few. Popular actors [[Ramon Revilla]] and [[Rudy Fernandez (actor)|Rudy Fernandez]] topped the list of action stars who appeared in one movie after another, portraying infamous and villainous characters. Other stars followed, such as [[Ace Vergel]], [[Jess Lapid, Jr.]], [[Rhene Imperial]] and Anthony Alonzo.\n\nAlonzo was one of the busiest actors during that time and made a long list of true-to-life movies based on factual events and police records. Stardom came late for Alonzo. He was already 30 when he was given an important role in Hindi sa Iyo ang Mundo Baby Porcuna in 1978, for which he was nominated for the URIAN Best Supporting Actor award. He was nominated in the FAMAS the following year for Dakpin si Junior Bombay (1979). In 1982, he won the FAMAS Best Actor award for his role in Bambang. He also won the Best Actor awards in the 3 Metro Manila Film Festival (MMFF) for his work in: ''Bago Kumalat Ang Kamandag'' (1983), ''The Moises Padilla Story: The Missing Chapter'' (1985) and ''Anak Badjao'' (1987).\n\n==Political life==\nHe ran for councilor in the 1992 Metro Manila elections and won. He served for two terms (1992&ndash;1998).\n\n==Filmography==\n===Movies===\n*Muntinlupa 1950 (1974)\n*Hide and Seek (1976)\n*Tatlong Kasalanan (1976)\n*Susan Kelly, Edad 20 (1977)\n*Hindi Sa Iyo ang Mundo, Baby Porcuna (1978)\n*Dakpin si Junior Bombay (1979)\n*Reyna ng Pitong Gatang (1980)\n*Diablong Sagrado (1980)\n*Kamlon (1981) [[Hadji Kamlon]]\n*Hanapin si Jake Romano (1981)\n*Dakpin si Pusa (1981)\n*Intrusion: Cambodia (1981)\n*Totoy Scarface (1981)\n*Bangkusay Tondo (1981)\n*Deathrow (1981)\n*Bambang (1982)\n*Bago Kumalat ang Kamandag (1983)\n*Target: Batang Sindikato (1983)\n*The Fighting Mayor (1983)\n*Warren Balane (1983)\n*W (1983)\n*Manila Gangwar (1984)\n*Sendong Sungkit (1984) Sendong\n*Kumander Cobra (1984)\n*Batang Quiricada (1984)\n*Diegong Bayong (1984)\n*Mianong Magat (1984)\n*Mad Warrior (1985)\n*Street Warrior (1985)\n*Alyas Junior Buang: Mad Killer Ng Visayas (1985) Junior Buang\n*Berong Bulag: Terror ng Bulacan (1985) Berong Bulag\n*Moises Padilla Story: The Missing Chapter (1985)\n*Manila Gang War (1985)\n*Clash of the Warlords (1985)\n*Victor Lopez ng Bangkusay (1986) Victor Lopez\n*Jailbreak 1958 (1987)\n*Anak Badjao (1987)\n*Dugo ng Pusakal (1988)\n*Trident Force (1988) Rashid\n*Ang Paghihiganti ni David Burdado (1988)\n*Jabidah Massacre (1990)\n*Irampa si Mediavillo (1990)\n*Hulihin si Boy Amores (1990) Boy Amores\n*Tawilwil Gang (1991)\n*Relaks Lang, Sagot Kita (1994) Warlito Gan\n*Costales (1995)\n*Demolisyon (1995)\n*Iligpit si Bobby Ortega: Markang Bungo 2(1995) Lando\n*Matira ang Matibay (1995)\n*Angel on Fire (1995)\n*Tong-Its (1996)\n*Ang Mamatay ng Dahil Sa Iyo (1996)\n*Masdan Mo Ang Mga Bata (1997) - his last movie\n\n==Health==\nIt was during this period in 1992 that he suffered from acute gastroenteritis.\n\n==Death==\nHe died of skin cancer on October 9, 1998, and was buried in [[Quezon City]].\n\n==Awards==\n{|| width=\"90%\" class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! width=\"10%\"| Year\n! width=\"20%\"| Award Giving Body\n! width=\"15%\"| Category\n! width=\"35%\"| Work\n! width=\"10%\"| Result\n|-\n|align=\"center\"| [[1983 Metro Manila Film Festival|1983]]\n|rowspan=3 align=\"center\"| [[Metro Manila Film Festival]] \n| align=\"center\" rowspan=3| [[Metro Manila Film Festival Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| align=\"center\"| ''Bago Kumalat ang Kamandag''<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1983 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1983\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[1985 Metro Manila Film Festival|1985]]\n| align=\"center\"| ''Moises Padilla Story: The Missing Chapter''<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1985/ \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1985\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| [[1987 Metro Manila Film Festival|1987]]\n| align=\"center\"| ''Anak Badjao''<ref>[https://www.imdb.com/event/ev0000431/1987 \"Metro Manila Film Festival:1987\"]. ''IMDB''. Retrieved 2014-04-09.</ref>\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{FAMAS Award for Best Actor}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alonzo, Anthony}}\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:1998 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Quezon City]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Metro Manila]]\n[[Category:Filipino male singers]]\n[[Category:Deaths from cancer in the Philippines]]\n[[Category:20th-century Filipino male actors]]\n[[Category:Filipino actor-politicians]]\n[[Category:Quezon City Council members]]\n[[Category:Deaths from skin cancer]]\n[[Category:Map\u00faa University alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century singers]]\n[[Category:20th-century male singers]]\n[[Category:Filipino male film actors]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Filipino actor, singer, and politician}}{{More citations needed|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name        = Anthony Alonzo\n|image       =\n|caption     =\n|birth_name  = Antonio Viana Hernandez\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date|1948|4|2}}\n|birth_place = [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n|death_date  = {{Death date and age|1998|10|9|1948|4|2}}\n|death_place = [[Quezon City]], Philippines\n|other_names = Tonio, Tony\n|known_for   = Former action star\n|occupation  = Actor, politician, singer\n|yearsactive = 1974\u20131998\n|nationality = [[Philippine nationality law|Filipino]]\n|parents     = {{ubl|Alfredo Hernandez {{small|(father)}}|Lourdes Viana {{small|(mother)}}}}\n|relatives   = {{ubl|[[Alicia Alonzo]] {{small|(sister)}}|[[Jon Hernandez]] {{small|(nephew)}}}}\n}}\n\n'''Antonio Viana Alonzo''' (April 2, 1948 \u2013 October 9, 1998), also known as '''Anthony''' and '''Tony''', was a Filipino actor, singer, and councilor of [[Quezon City]].\n\n==Early life==\nHe was born as Antonio Viana Hernandez on April 2, 1948, in [[Quezon City]] to Alfredo Hernandez and Lourdes Viana. He is the brother of actress [[Alicia Alonzo]], who herself is still appearing in Filipino films and soaps.\n\n==Education==\nAntonio V. Hernandez received his elementary and secondary education at the Marulas Elementary School and Espiritu Santo High School, respectively. He took up Commerce at the Mapua Institute of Technology.\n\n==Movie career==\nBesides the so-called bold and sexy films that pervaded the movie industry in the '70s and early '80s, the period also saw the emergence and proliferation of true-to-life movies. Producers then banked on the colorful and controversial lives of known notorious criminals to come up with profitable movie projects, i.e. Nardong Putik, Kapitan Eddie Set, Baby Ama, Ronquillo, Salonga, and Waway, to name a few. Popular actors [[Ramon Revilla]] and [[Rudy Fernandez (actor)|Rudy Fernandez]] topped the list of action stars who appeared in one movie after another, portraying infamous and villainous characters. Other stars followed, such as [[Ace Vergel]], [[Jess Lapid, Jr.]], [[Rhene Imperial]] and Anthony Alonzo.\n\nAlonzo was one of the busiest actors during that time and made a long list of true-to-life movies based on factual events and police records. Stardom came late for Alonzo. He was already 30 when he was given an important role in Hindi sa Iyo ang Mundo Baby Porcuna in 1978, for which he was nominated for the URIAN Best Supporting Actor award. He was nominated in the FAMAS the following year for Dakpin si Junior Bombay (1979). In 1982, he won the FAMAS Best Actor award for his role in Bambang. He also won the Best Actor awards in the 3 Metro Manila Film Festival (MMFF) for his work in: ''Bago Kumalat Ang Kamandag'' (1983), ''The Moises Padilla Story: The Missing Chapter'' (1985) and ''Anak Badjao'' (1987).\n\n==Political life==\nHe ran for councilor in the 1992 Metro Manila elections and won. He served for two terms (1992&ndash;1998).\n\n==Filmography==\n===Movies===\n*Muntinlupa 1950 (1974)\n*Hide and Seek (1976)\n*Tatlong Kasalanan (1976)\n*Susan Kelly, Edad 20 (1977)\n*Hindi Sa Iyo ang Mundo, Baby Porcuna (1978)\n*Dakpin si Junior Bombay (1979)\n*Reyna ng Pitong Gatang (1980)\n*Diablong Sagra