{"title_page": "Borno State University", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n |name              = Borno State University\n|native_name       = \n |image_name        = \n |image_size        =\n |caption           =\n |motto             = \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645 \u0644\u064a\u0633 \u0644\u0647 \u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f ''[[Arabic]]''\n|mottoeng           = knowledge has no boundary\n |established       = 2016\n |type              = Public\n |chancellor        = Mohammed Indimi\n |vice_chancellor   = Prof. Umar Kyari Sandabe\n |faculty           = \n |staff             =\n |students          =\n |city              = [[Maiduguri]]\n |state             = [[Borno State]]\n |country           = [[Nigeria]]\n |campus            = \n |former_names      = \n |website           = {{Official website|http://www.bosu.edu.ng/}}\n}}\n\n'''Borno State University''' is in [[Maiduguri]], [[Borno State]], [[Nigeria]]. It was established in 2016.<ref>[https://www.nta.ng/news/20161107-unc-approves-borno-state-university-take-off \"NUC Approves Borno State University Take off\"] ''[[Nigerian Television Authority|NTA]], Maiduguri, 07 November, 2016 ''Retrieved 06 April, 2019</ref><ref>[https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/nuc-approves-borno-state-university \"NUC Approves Borno State University\"] ''[[Daily Trust]]'' Maiduguri. Borno State</ref> It has five faculties with over 20 [[Academic department|departments]]. The pioneer and current vice chancellor of the university is Prof. [[Umar Kyari Sandabe]].<ref>[https://www.channelstv.com/tag/borno-states-university \" Borno State University \"] ''Channels Television'' Borno State, Nigeria.</ref><ref>[https://www.channelstv.com/2016/11/07/nuc-approves-borno-state-university-takeoff \"NUC Approves Borno State University Takeoff \"] Channels Television.</ref>\n\n==Faculties==\n* Faculty of Sciences\n* Faculty of Management \n* Faculty of Arts\n* Faculty of Social Science\n* Faculty of Education\n* Faculty of Engineering\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.bosu.edu.ng/ Borno State University official website]\n\n{{Universities in Nigeria}}\n\n{{coord missing|Nigeria}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Nigeria]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2016]]\n[[Category:2016 establishments in Nigeria]]\n\n\n{{Nigeria-university-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox University\n |name              = Borno State University\n|native_name       = \n |image_name        = \n |image_size        =\n |caption           =\n |motto             = \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645 \u0644\u064a\u0633 \u0644\u0647 \u062d\u062f\u0648\u062f ''[[Arabic]]''\n|mottoeng           = knowledge has no boundary\n |established       = 2016\n |type              = Public\n |chancellor        = Mohammed Indimi\n |vice_chancellor   = Prof. Umar Kyari Sandabe\n |faculty           = \n |staff             =\n |students          =\n |city              = [[Maiduguri]]\n |state             = [[Borno State]]\n |country           = [[Nigeria]]\n |campus            = \n |former_names      = \n |website           = {{Official website|http://www.bosu.edu.ng/}}\n}}\n\n'''Borno State University''' is in [[Maiduguri]], [[Borno State]], [[Nigeria]]. It was established in 2016.<ref> [https://www.nta.ng/news/20161107-unc-approves-borno-state-university-take-off \"NUC Approves Borno State University Take off\"] ''[[Nigerian Television Authority|NTA]], Maiduguri, 07 November, 2016 ''Retrieved 06 April, 2019</ref><ref> [https://www.dailytrust.com.ng/nuc-approves-borno-state-university \"NUC Approves Borno State University\"] ''[[Daily Trust]]'' Maiduguri. Borno State</ref> It has five faculties with over 20 [[Academic department|departments]]. The pioneer and current vice chancellor of the university is Prof. [[Umar Kyari Sandabe]].<ref>[https://www.channelstv.com/tag/borno-states-university \" Borno State University \"] ''Channels Television'' Borno State, Nigeria.</ref><ref>[https://